NNAAMMEE
     df - disk free

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
     ddff [ --ii ] [ filesystem ... ] [ file ... ]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
     _D_f prints out the amount of free disk space available on the
     specified _f_i_l_e_s_y_s_t_e_m, e.g. ``/dev/rp0a'', or on the filesys-
     tem in which the specified _f_i_l_e, e.g. ``$HOME'', is con-
     tained.  If no file system is specified, the free space on
     all of the normally mounted file systems is printed.  The
     reported numbers are in kilobytes.

     Other options are:

     --ii   Report also the number of inodes which are used and
	  free.

FFIILLEESS
     /etc/fstab     list of normally mounted filesystems

